    <Content contentid="4140" contenttypeid="DNNG" desc="Dining">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Thai cuisine is celebrated the world over for its flavourful dishes, and Villa Rodnaya is the perfect place to explore Thai gastronomic delights under the talented direction of the in-villa chef.&nbsp; Adventurous eaters, children, and those who crave their favourite home-cooked foods are all catered to, with meals at Rodnaya fully customised to each guest’s preference.</p><p>Find Thai food, set breakfasts and Western food in the villa’s suggestion menu, with an enticing selection of dishes including <span style="font-style: italic;">tom kha gai</span> (delicious chicken soup made with coconut milk and fragrant galangal); <span style="font-style: italic;">gaeng phed ped yang</span> (red curry with roasted duck); <span style="font-style: italic;">pla thod ta rod</span> (crispy sea bass with five-flavour sauce), and the chef’s specialty <span style="font-style: italic;">Gaeng ka ree nue fak tong</span> (beef tenderloin and pumpkin in Thai yellow curry). </p><p>The chef and kitchen team take care of all the grocery shopping, and they know exactly where to find the freshest and best quality ingredients.&nbsp; Provisions are charged at cost plus a 20% handling fee and a government tax, and guests are requested to provide cash to cover groceries in advance.&nbsp; The staff will keep receipts for reference when settling the bills.</p><p>Villa Rodnaya’s design elegance and magical views give every meal some added finesse whether dining in its vaulted-roof indoor dining area or on the breezy pool terrace.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4141" contenttypeid="FAM" desc="Families">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Rodnaya was designed with families in mind and the villa brims with both playful and practical features for a worry-free and fun family holiday.</p>  <p>Having a private 18-metre pool to splash around in is sure to be a family highlight, and, rare for Phuket villas, it’s surrounded by fencing to keep the wee ones safe.&nbsp; The villa’s playroom is stocked with toys and games for air-conditioned fun, while the media room is a cosy place to gather for some cartoon or movie-watching sessions.</p><p>There’s no need to worry about travelling with cumbersome children’s equipment as the villa is well equipped with a baby cot, changing table, safety stair gate, high chair, baby bath facilities and toilet trainer seat.&nbsp; Other items may be sourced from local rental agencies for a small extra fee – just let us know your requirements when making your villa reservation.&nbsp; Likewise, if you’re needing a night out during your stay, a reliable babysitting service can be arranged (extra charges apply).</p><p>Rodnaya’s modern guest kitchen and private chef make it easy to ensure the young ones are well fed.&nbsp; Kids can select from the villa menu, and the chef will adjust ingredients where necessary to make them child-friendly. Thai favourites such as chicken satay, mango sticky rice and pad Thai noodles provide a great opportunity to discover new tastes.</p><p>Though families staying at Rodnaya have plenty to enjoy within the villa, the soft sands of nearby Nai Thon beckon for beach adventures.&nbsp; Spend the day running around barefoot and building sandcastles on this uncrowded beach, or stop by one of the beachside food stands for a fresh coconut and some grilled Thai snacks.&nbsp; Kid-friendly water sports including snorkelling and stand-up paddling are available at the beach, while for more family activity ideas check our <a target="_self" href="./the-locale/things-to-do.html">Things to Do</a> page or consult with your villa manager.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4142" contenttypeid="SPA" desc="Spa">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>With its tranquil setting and inspiring views, Villa Rodnaya is a fabulous venue for a restorative spa or beauty treatment.&nbsp; Ease the senses with a massage, manicure or other spa therapy in complete privacy in one of Rodnaya’s bedrooms or living areas, or enjoy the sea breezes with an outdoor treatment on the pool terrace.</p>  <p>To book your private villa spa session, simply browse the menu and then ask the villa manager to arrange it.&nbsp; Among the many treatments on offer are traditional Thai massage, oil massage, foot massages, body scrubs, pedicures and manicures.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4189" contenttypeid="LCTN" desc="Location / Locale">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>The crystal-clear waters of the Andaman Sea and the powder-soft sands  of Nai Thon Beach are in full view from every villa and residence at  Malaiwana.&nbsp; Just a short walk or downhill drive away from the estate,  this pristine one-kilometre-long beach on Phuket’s peaceful northwest  coast is perfect for sunning, swimming, snorkelling, stand-up paddling  and sandcastle building.&nbsp; A tranquil village atmosphere prevails in this  unspoiled corner of the island and the beach road is lined with low-key  shops and cafés.&nbsp; Along the coast, numerous hidden coves and beaches  are waiting to be discovered.</p><p>Just up the road, the Trisara Resort  offers fabulous dining, and other chic nearby venues include Dream  Beach Club at Layan Beach and the beachfront restaurants at Bang Tao,  eight kilometres to the south. </p><p>Malaiwana is an easy 20-minute drive from Phuket International Airport.</p>]]></Description>
